author: hdmoadmin
title: State Football first-round pairings released
text:
2:45 pm - October 24, 2015 State Football first-round pairings released 
Staff Report 
The first-round pairings for the State Football playoffs have been released following the final games of the regular season, which were played on Friday. The State qualifiers from area teams are Dallas Center-Grimes, Van Meter and Waukee and the State Playoffs start on Wednesday, Oct. 28. 
Van Meter (8-1, 6-0 District 8) kicks off their State Playoff run against Manson Northwest Webster (3-6) on Wednesday. This will be the first meeting of the season between the two teams. 
DC-G (7-2, 5-1 District 8) will host Carlisle (6-3) in Grimes. The Mustangs started the season with a big 39-6 over Carlisle back on Friday, Aug. 28. 
The Warriors (7-2, 6-0 District 4) will play hosts to Sioux City East in the first round of the playoffs. This will be the first meeting of the season between the two teams as well. 
All three first-round playoff games begin at 7 p.m. on Wednesday, Oct. 28.
